BFN 

  [Excerpt] Algiers, June 7 (AFP) -- An Algerian journalist 
was shot dead on Tuesday in central Algiers, the security 
services announced. 
  Cherquit Ferhat of the government daily El Moudjahid was the 
14th journalist to be murdered since May 1993 in attacks 
generally blamed by authorities on Islamic extremists. 
  Security officials gave no details of the circumstances of 
the killing. 
  Cherquit, 45, who had worked on the paper for many years and 
was married with children, was gunned down in the open street, 
media sources told AFP. 

